The last time the juniors were on the courts competitively was in November 2020 when Tennis Kenya held the Senior and Junior challenge series tournament after almost nine months of inactivity. The first of an eight series tournament that ran between November 23 and December 10 featured both men and women and saw some of Kenya's top talent turn up to compete at the Nairobi Club under strict Covid-19 rules and regulations. Kenya will host the the first ever International Tennis Federation (ITF) World Junior Circuit at the Nairobi Club.
The debut outdoor clay court event will be played across eight weeks this year. Three weeks in January, two in July and three in November respectively. The January event is scheduled to start on the 18th and run for three straight weeks with 17 countries participating including India, France, Russia, Norway alongside the hosts.



