Derick Ominde, Jayson Mbongoro, Kael Shalin Shah, Raymond Oduor, Brandon Sagala and Reesh Haria will show up for the boys' category.
The last time the juniors were on the courts competitively was in November 2020 when Tennis Kenya held the Senior and Junior challenge series tournament after almost nine months of inactivity.
 The first of an eight series tournament that ran between November 23 and December 10 featured both men and women and saw some of Kenya's top talent turn up to compete at the Nairobi Club under strict Covid-19 rules and regulations.
The round robin series in the finals of the Junior challenge series saw the pair of Reha Kipsang and Faith Urasa lead the standings with six points off three wins in a total of six sets played.
In the boys' doubles category, the pair of Reesh Haria and Sahil Chana downed the duo of Benjamin Tekeo and James Kang’ethe in two straight sets of 6-0/6-0 in just under an hour of play.
The 10th Nairobi International Junior Circuit and the 12th Kenya International Junior Circuit are expected to follow up as the calendar of events rolls over. Nduku is optimistic that the federation will host three international events in January. This is the first of an eight-series tournament consisting of four senior events and four junior events. Judge allows withdrawal of petition that had blocked Ms Ann Mwenda from being vetted. The ICC has the authority to hear cases of war crimes, genocide and crimes against humanity committed in the 123 countries, including Uganda. In December, TSC failed to attend a negotiation meeting called by Labour CS Simon Chelugui to mediate the two parties.